    "question_id" : 79621097,
    "body" : "<p>The steps are the following</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Add your certificates into a <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Java_KeyStore\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Java Keystore</a></li>\n<li>Point JMeter to use the keystore by setting <code>javax.net.ssl.keyStore</code> and <code>javax.net.ssl.keyStorePassword</code> system properties</li>\n<li>Add <a href=\"https://jmeter.apache.org/usermanual/component_reference.html#Keystore_Configuration\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">Keystore Configuration</a> element which will traverse the certificates in the keystore and use the different certificate for each JMeter thread (virtual user)</li>\n</ol>\n<p>More information:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.blazemeter.com/blog/client-side-performance-testing-using-jmeter\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">How to Set Your JMeter Load Test to Use Client Side Certificates</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://dzone.com/articles/how-to-use-multiple-certificates-when-load-testing\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">How to Use Multiple Certificates When Load Testing Secure Websites</a></li>\n</ul>\n",
